}

    echo ""
    echo "ğŸ§¹ Cleaning up..."
    if [ ! -z "$NGROK_PID" ]; then

    exit 0

# Check if we're in the right directory

        echo "âŒ Failed to install dependencies"

echo ""

    echo "âš ï¸  ngrok not found. Installing ngrok..."

        # macOS
        if command_exists brew; then
            brew install ngrok/ngrok/ngrok
        else
            echo "âŒ Please install Homebrew first or install ngrok manually from https://ngrok.com/"
            exit 1

    elif [[ "$OSTYPE" == "linux-gnu"* ]]; then
        # Linux
        echo "Please install ngrok manually from https://ngrok.com/ or use your package manager"
        echo "For Ubuntu/Debian: snap install ngrok"
        exit 1
    else
        echo "âŒ Unsupported OS. Please install ngrok manually from https://ngrok.com/"
        exit 1
    fi
fi

# Kill any existing ngrok processes
pkill -f "ngrok http" 2>/dev/null || true
sleep 2

echo "ğŸŒ Starting ngrok tunnel on port 8080..."
ngrok http 8080 --log=stdout > ngrok.log 2>&1 &
NGROK_PID=$!

echo "â³ Waiting for ngrok to start..."
sleep 5

# Get the ngrok URL
echo "ğŸ” Retrieving ngrok URL..."
NGROK_URL=""
for i in {1..10}; do
    # Try to get the URL from ngrok API
    NGROK_URL=$(curl -s http://localhost:4040/api/tunnels 2>/dev/null | grep -o '"public_url":"[^"]*https://[^"]*"' | grep https | head -1 | cut -d'"' -f4)
    
    if [ ! -z "$NGROK_URL" ]; then

    exit 1

echo "âœ… ngrok tunnel established!"

echo "================================================"

echo "   Local:  http://localhost:8080"
echo "   Public: $NGROK_URL"
echo "================================================"
echo ""
echo "Press Ctrl+C to stop all services"
echo ""

# Start the development server
npm run dev
